Project code: GPL-3.0-or-later.

The package includes a checksum-pinned copy of Rufus 4.15's uefi-ntfs.img so
manual NTFS media can use the same architecture-aware UEFI:NTFS boot path. The
associated upstream readme and component licensing information are installed in
/usr/share/doc/rufusarm64/uefi-ntfs/.

The helper also embeds byte arrays derived from Rufus 4.15's GPL ms-sys Windows
7 MBR, NTFS PBR, and FAT32 Windows PE PBR source. The exact upstream source
fragments, commit pin, and SHA-256 manifest are installed in
/usr/share/doc/rufusarm64/ms-sys/ and included in the source release.

The source tree also retains the minimal FreeDOS 1.4 `KERNEL.SYS` and
`COMMAND.COM` bytes reviewed against Rufus 4.15. The official package metadata,
GPLv2 texts, complete corresponding source archives, extraction tool, and
checksum manifest are retained under vendor/freedos/. These files are not yet
installed as a runtime feature or exposed by the graphical application.
